# Regulatory Compliance Checklist

This checklist helps organizations ensure compliance with key cybersecurity regulations, including PCI DSS, GDPR, and SOX. Use this list to audit your current compliance status and implement necessary security controls.

## 1. PCI DSS (Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard):
- [ ] Implement and maintain a firewall to protect cardholder data.
- [ ] Encrypt cardholder data using strong cryptography (e.g., AES-256).
- [ ] Implement access control measures to restrict access to cardholder data.
- [ ] Regularly test security systems and processes.

## 2. GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation):
- [ ] Obtain explicit consent for processing personal data.
- [ ] Ensure data subjects can access, rectify, or erase their personal data.
- [ ] Implement privacy by design in systems architecture.
- [ ] Appoint a Data Protection Officer (DPO) if required.

## 3. SOX (Sarbanes-Oxley Act):
- [ ] Implement logging and monitoring to ensure accurate financial reporting.
- [ ] Perform periodic security audits and internal controls testing.
- [ ] Restrict access to systems that impact financial reporting.
- [ ] Maintain a comprehensive disaster recovery plan.

By ensuring adherence to these standards, your organization can mitigate legal risks and enhance customer trust.

